task.summary: Default task
Integrating VCS with intellij
Configuration now sends to mongodb
Submission from Nexus user now stores in mongodb
Added all new files
Moved retrieval service (for GitHub partial) into a separate service.
Integrated with Nexus so that requests are returned with sample feedback
First implementation of allocation algorithm. Needs testing and confirmation it works - probably doesn't but good skeleton to work from.
Added seeds and devbase. Seeds to seed db and devbase for any contained js issues
Allocation algorithm seems to work, just needs to be limited so that pid is kept as low as possible across all current submissions
Allocation algorithm seems to work, just needs to be limited so that pid is kept as low as possible across all current submissions
Have written a recursive algorithm to successfully store to pid to db. Now need to re-implement alloc algo
Appears to be a successful allocation and no starvation :)

Working allocation algorithm. Slight issue of stack overflowing if same submission occurs multiple times. This needs handling. Also need to look at what happens if a student uploads a new submission, how should this be handled? - allocate as though they are an entirely new submission - remove their old submission and reallocate to previously allocated student - remove their old submission and allocate to new student

Have refactored code a bit and re-designed for a 4 view system. The allocation view, the provider view (with submission and form), the receiver view (view their submission and the feedback associated). and the configuration view. Will also need to built a view for the academic.
Fixed allocation view. It will get the submission for each pid. It currently matches on studentuids, now need to pass through to provider view

Finally making some headway with saving the user filled data. By storing in JSON and using 'hack', have been able to build a mechanism of serialization and de-serialization. Now need to implement (possibly two directives/factories, one for rendering and one for saving) for both provider and receiver.

Rendering and saving directives implemented. Changed pids to objects to allow for 'currentForm'. Given currentForm to said object when form is submitted by student. currentForm is json of the form submitted.
Provider MVP is essentially built. Need to finish up on receiver and tie it all together with routing.
Received view built, now to render the JSON form
Refactored configuration directory
MVP complete. Need to integrate with Nexus and then need to seal up
Trying to build a view to test with MVP. MVP seems to be functioning as expected
Refactored all $http calls to be in separate angularjs factories
